The paper focuses on the field of collaborative robotics and human-robot interaction, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes a deep learning approach for localising and estimating the 3D position of a robot in 2D camera images, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also mentions the identification of the robot type, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) methods. Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed approach in human-robot interaction, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
